messages.subject: Ohio and driving
messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 5/20/03 5:42:17 AM, homemama@infinet.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 5/20/03 5:42:17 AM, homemama@... writes:

<< Ohio? Did I see Ohio? LOL! When? For a Ren Fest? Friends? A conference?

I know I'm nosey.<BWWG> Hey I bet I could get a one day thing together here

if you're interested. >>

Just to take a drive, and visit Carol Narigon & family.

Marty will get a learner's permit next winter. Unlike Kirby, Marty is
unemployed, and we could get all his practice driving done in one fell swoop
if we leave town. <g>

I don't know Ohio very well so I don't know how far you might be from Carol.
All I know is there are huge rivers, too many trees, and all the major cities
start with "C" and have long names, so they confused me (ON purpose, FOR
meanness).

We've been talking about it like it's definite, but not talking about a date,
except saying maybe early April, give or take a month.

It would be GREAT to do a one-day conference or presentation or whatever,
especially if I could pass the hat for gas and food money or some such.

My greatest fear is a breakdown, because we don't have a new car. Twice in
my life I've had new cars, and this isn't one of those times.

Sandra
